message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Comoros in the past 20 years was the political crisis that occurred in 2001. In April 2001, a group of rebels led by Colonel Azali Assoumani seized power in a coup d'état, ousting then-President Tadjidine Ben Said Massounde. This event led to political instability and a period of transitional governments. Eventually, in 2002, Assoumani won presidential elections and became the elected president. This event had a profound impact on the political landscape of Comoros and had long-lasting effects on the country's governance and stability.
